 Indian Penal Code, 1860: Section 302-Appellant convicted of murder of lady and son-Death sentence by trial court-Confirmed by High Court-Courts below-Whether right in imposing death penalty-Mitigating circumstances-Unfortunate relationship between deceased, an elderly lady and appellant, in mid 20s-Sudden spurning by partner-Appellant experiencing disappointment of discarded lover-Vicious effect of film picturising violence seen by appellant- Supreme Court converting death sentence to life imprisonment.
 
